Kassi is a service that enables borrowing, buying, selling and giving
away items and the exchange of various favors. Users of Kassi can list
their items they could lend, their expertise, and other things they
could do in their profiles. These are then shown in searchable and
browsable lists. If something you require is not already present in
Kassi, you can post a request.

Ossi is a group-centered mobile social media service. You can use Ossi
to connect with friends, keep in touch with groups and to stay tuned
to what is sizzling around you.

The NordSecMob service is desiged to make life easier for new incoming
students by providing practical daily life information during their
study period. It has user interfaces for mobile and desktop browsers,
rich content-based forum with Map tag functionality, and social
networking interface to express your feelings. Although the service is
mainly designed for mobility focused Master's programs
(e.g. NordSecMob), it is certainly a handy tool for all new
international members of the university.

Mobile HUBI Portal offers context-aware services in the Helsinki capital area, on your mobile phone. Available services include a public transport route guide that allows using your current location and own places as shortcuts, and a Helsinki area event recommender including also the Aalto University events. The service portal is provided for pilot use and developed further by VTT as part of a project studying ubiquitous mobile services.

All the services are parts of OtaSizzle, a project of TKK and HIIT.
OtaSizzle is funded by the Technology for Life campaign of TKK with
donations from private companies and communities. The purpose of the
project is to study the development and use of social web services.

